commentTextItems.html: That's it! it's all over! that was full on leg stump, whipped away off the pads wide of mid wicket, and Sri Lanka have won this game comprehensively

commentPostTextItems.html: Sri Lanka have completed a clinical nine-wicket win here. Zimbabwe have only themselves to blame for their appalling batting display, and will hope to come back strongly in the next match.
Prosper Utseya: "We wanted to bat first after we batted well in the first 15 overs of the previous game. We need to do our homework, and we hope for a better performance in the next game"
Mahela Jayawardene: "This was a much improved performance from our last game and it was good to see our fast bowlers coming to the party this time."
Ajantha Mendis is the Man of the Match for his haul of 4 for 15.

That's it folks! Thanks for joining us today and lets all hope for a more exciting fixture on the 24th when these two teams meet again. Until then, it's goodbye from Siddhartha Talya on the commentary and Chaminda D'Silva on the scoring desk. Adios!

commentTextItems.html: full on middle and leg, pushed wide of mid on for a quick single
shot! that was short of a length outside off, Sangakkara steps down the track and swats that wide of the bowler to the long off boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: It's started raining in Harare now. What a twist to the tale

commentTextItems.html: short outside off, Sangakkara wants to finish this off early, tries to cut it over point, gets an outside edge wide of third man for a boundary
full on middle and off, tries to drive it down towards mid on, gets an inside edge onto his pads
back of a length outside leg stump, flicked away to fine leg
pitched short of a good length outside leg stump, walks across to glance it towards fine leg, clips the pads on the way to the keeper
shot! that was full, just slightly outside the off stump, Tharanga plants his foot forward and drives that beautifully wide of a diving mid off for a boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: The Sri Lankan innings set to resume

commentTextItems.html: good length outside off and swinging away, left alone
tossed up on the off stump and spinning away, left alone.

commentPostTextItems.html: Sri Lanka set for a resounding win here, but they'll have to wait a little over 40 minutes to resume their innings and knock off the remaining 16 runs
We've got our own Facebook page now, go on there and discuss this game and cricket with other cricket fans

commentTextItems.html: flighted outside off, pushed between cover and point for a single
flighted on middle and off, driven down the ground to long on
tossed up on off and spins away, Sangakkara gets forward to defend but that just about escapes the outside edge
flighted on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, pitches on a full length, driven to cover
short of a good length outside off, shoulders arms
good length outside off, left alone this time
beaten! good length bowled at a good pace outside off, swung away after pitching, tries to defend, but didn't anticipate the swing there
full on the pads, drives it wide of mid on for a couple

dismissalComment.html: gone!! bowled 'im!! that went straight on, bowled with a flatter trajectory on middle stump, Taibu anticipating an off spinner tried to work it away towards square leg, but the ball held its line, missed Taibu's bat, and crashed into middle and off stump.

headshotImage.caption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura lbw b Mendis 3 (27b 0x4 0x6 36m) SR: 11.11

dismissalComment.html: gone! that was pitched on a good length on middle stump, held its line, Chigumbura expecting it to spin towards him, tries to drive it back to the bowler, but the ball goes straight on and strikes his back pad, hits him in line with middle stump, and a delayed appeal by Mendis is upheld by Aleem Dar

headshotImage.caption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Thilan Thushara  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya c †Sangakkara b Thushara 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone!! We seem to be heading for another early finish here! that was bowled on a good length outside off and leaving the right hander, comes forward to defend but gets a thin outside edge to Sangakkara who takes the easiest of catches

dismissalText.commentary: Ray Price c Jayawardene b Thushara 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: gone!! that was pitched on a good length outside off and angling away, Price has a lethargic prod at it, gets the outside edge and Jayawardene at first slip takes a good catch diving forward and to his left. Eight down now!

headshotImage.caption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tawanda Mupariwa c Jayawardene b Mendis 1 (9b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 11.11

dismissalComment.html: pitches on a good length on the off stump and spinning in, Mupariwa gets on his knees and tries to sweep that fine, deflects off the glove and the ball lobs in the air and over the keeper, Jayawardene at first slip runs a few steps to his left to take an easy catch. Mendis strikes immediately

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Maharoof b Mendis 10 (37b 0x4 0x6 48m) SR: 27.02

dismissalComment.html: gone!! all over!! that was flighted on the off stump, Williams planted his foot forward and tried to loft that one over mid on, Maharoof remained alert and ran behind to take a well judged catch

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga not out 26 (57b 2x4 0x6 71m) SR: 45.61
Mahela Udawatte c Masakadza b Mupariwa 7 (24b 0x4 0x6 31m) SR: 29.16

dismissalComment.html: gone!! full outside off and swinging away just a touch, tempting the batsman to go for a drive, Udawatte tries to do exactly that, gets an outside edge and Masakadza at first slip makes no mistake.
